"Some notes on introducing J with statistical examples"
is a 49-page paper giving an introduction to the J
dialect of APL by means of some simple examples from
probability and statistics including arithmetic,
geometric and harmonic means, variance, median and
quartiles, frequency tables and barcharts, simulation of
dice-rolling experiments, probability distributions, 
linear regression, and analysis of variance. The file
"intj.ps" is a Postscript file containing the text of the
paper, and "intj.js" is an ASCII file giving the script
for the J objects used in the paper.

